"{\"uid\": \"timesrepublican.com-opinion-columnists-2024-08-no-bragging-on-this-olympics-iowa-angle\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Aug 6, 2024  Photo by Jared Strong/Iowa Capital Dispatch The North Raccoon River routinely has elevated levels of nitrate contamination.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During the 40 years I was a newspaper editor/manager, I strived to ensure the staff incorporated context into their articles.\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes, in a journalistic shorthand, that was described \\\"the Iowa angle.\\\"\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 328, \"end\": 332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If there was a mass murder in Iowa, I would dip into my stash of clippings and find the list of the worst mass killings in Iowa history.\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 372, \"end\": 376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That allowed us to give context to the magnitude of the tragedy.\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The same with tornadoes and floods.\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How does the number of deaths compare with the worst of these nightmares we have experienced in the past?\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During the Vietnam War, and later during the Gulf wars, we turned to bound desk calendars where we pasted clippings to track the running tally of deaths of Iowa soldiers.\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, over this past weekend a friend and I pawed through statistics to provide important Iowa context when Belgium's mixed relay triathlon team pulled out of the Olympic competition in Paris.\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 948, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999945434865, \"rank\": 5.43911329190894e-09, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1044, \"end\": 1049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.44388458386514e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Belgium's decision was made after one of its athletes became ill and was hospitalized, reportedly for an E. coli infection, after she swam in the River Seine earlier in the competition.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1237, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999945434865, \"rank\": 5.43911329190894e-09, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1198, \"end\": 1209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same day as the announcement about Claire Michel, Olympic organizers canceled a training session for the swimming leg of the triathlon because the Seine's water pollution levels were too high.\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1277, \"end\": 1290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Claire Michel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\"}, {\"begin\": 1389, \"end\": 1394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999990507093609, \"rank\": 9.492996593058805e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The quality of the Seine's water has been a persistent worry leading up to this year's Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999990507093609, \"rank\": 9.492996593058805e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pollution levels forced organizers to consider delaying, or even canceling, some outdoor swimming events.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is where the Iowa angle comes into the picture - and it provides some interesting context for the news out of Paris.\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 1764, \"end\": 1769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.44388458386514e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just as water quality stats for the Seine have fluctuated, based on the relationship between rainfall, runoff and drier weather, the quality of water at Iowa's beaches this summer has fluctuated, too.\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1808, \"end\": 1813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999990507093609, \"rank\": 9.492996593058805e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1925, \"end\": 1929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Iowa Department of Natural Resources specialists monitor water at beaches because poor water quality can cause intestinal problems that may develop into serious infections.\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As Claire Michel's experience shows, poor water quality should not be brushed aside and taken lightly.\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Claire Michel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claire_Michel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Contaminated water can lead even healthy young people to need medical treatment.\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is how the River Seine's pollution stats look when compared with some Iowa beaches, where the DNR has said at various times that swimming is not recommended because of the contamination.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2348, \"end\": 2359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2407, \"end\": 2411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 2431, \"end\": 2434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin_Department_of_Natural_Resources\", \"score\": 0.9999998926446154, \"rank\": 1.048898047531837e-07, \"text\": \"DNR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin_Department_of_Natural_Resources\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin_Department_of_Natural_Resources\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 31, the highest E. coli concentration along the Seine's race course was 649 MPN/100 mL.\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2581, \"end\": 2586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999990507093609, \"rank\": 9.492996593058805e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That measurement tallies the density of E. coli organisms per 100 milliliters of water.\", \"from\": 2621, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Iowa angle shows these readings from tests on July 30 or 31:  \\u2022 Hickory Grove Park, Story County - 24,000 MPN/100mL  \\u2022 Edson Park beach, Buena Vista County - 20,000  \\u2022 Awaysis beach, Storm Lake - 9,200  \\u2022 Bel Air beach, Buena Vista County - 3,900  \\u2022 Big Creek State Park, Polk County - 3,400  \\u2022 Gray's Lake, Des Moines - 3,000  \\u2022 Lake Iowa Park, Iowa County - 2,900  \\u2022 Lake Ahquabi State Park, Warren County: 2,100  \\u2022 Sandy Hollow Park, Sioux County - 1,500  \\u2022 Chautauqua beach, Storm Lake - 750  \\u2022 Lacey-Keosauqua State Park, Van Buren County - 660  \\u2022 Lake Wapello State Park, Davis County - 600  \\u2022 Lake of Three Fires State Park, Taylor County - 590  \\u2022 Beeds Lake, Franklin County - 540  \\u2022 Union Grove State Park, Tama County - 470  \\u2022 Lake Darling State Park, Washington County - 470  Unlike the Olympics, these comparisons between Paris and Iowa draw attention to persistent problems in our state that no one wants to celebrate.\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 3645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2714, \"end\": 2718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 2798, \"end\": 2810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Story_County,_Iowa\", \"score\": 0.9993114646608182, \"rank\": 0.0006870491240123192, \"text\": \"Story County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Story_County,_Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Story_County,_Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 2833, \"end\": 2838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edson_River\", \"score\": 0.9999996220127091, \"rank\": 3.454543369854899e-07, \"text\": \"Edson\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edson_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edson_River\"}, {\"begin\": 2897, \"end\": 2907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storm_Lake,_Iowa\", \"score\": 0.9900977067663816, \"rank\": 0.009999999999997917, \"text\": \"Storm Lake\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storm_Lake,_Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storm_Lake,_Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 3022, \"end\": 3032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Des_Moines_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.608795514383965e-20, \"text\": \"Des Moines\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Des_Moines_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Des_Moines_River\"}, {\"begin\": 3060, \"end\": 3071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa_County,_Wisconsin\", \"score\": 0.7304752357315362, \"rank\": 0.3679270581925054, \"text\": \"Iowa County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa_County,_Wisconsin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa_County,_Wisconsin\"}, {\"begin\": 3108, \"end\": 3121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warren_County,_New_Jersey\", \"score\": 0.8369450340147271, \"rank\": 0.06234849772999243, \"text\": \"Warren County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warren_County,_New_Jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warren_County,_New_Jersey\"}, {\"begin\": 3151, \"end\": 3163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sioux_County,_Iowa\", \"score\": 0.7558036640359694, \"rank\": 0.1700407213496014, \"text\": \"Sioux County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sioux_County,_Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sioux_County,_Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 3175, \"end\": 3185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chautauqua\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.9867270485922867e-12, \"text\": \"Chautauqua\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chautauqua\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chautauqua\"}, {\"begin\": 3193, \"end\": 3203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storm_Lake,_Iowa\", \"score\": 0.9900977067663816, \"rank\": 0.009999999999997917, \"text\": \"Storm Lake\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storm_Lake,_Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storm_Lake,_Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 3213, \"end\": 3239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lacey-Keosauqua_State_Park\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lacey-Keosauqua State Park\", \"types\": [\"Q473972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lacey-Keosauqua_State_Park\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lacey-Keosauqua_State_Park\"}, {\"begin\": 3430, \"end\": 3441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tama_County,_Iowa\", \"score\": 0.9999999856395335, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tama County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tama_County,_Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tama_County,_Iowa\"}, {\"begin\": 3548, \"end\": 3553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.44388458386514e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3558, \"end\": 3562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No one plans a trip to Paris to swim in the Seine.\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3670, \"end\": 3675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.44388458386514e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3691, \"end\": 3696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999990507093609, \"rank\": 9.492996593058805e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Eiffel Tower, yes.\", \"from\": 3698, \"to\": 3720, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Louvre and the thousands of restaurants that offer something much different from loose-meat sandwiches, yes, those are the pull for tourists and French locals alike.\", \"from\": 3721, \"to\": 3890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3725, \"end\": 3731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.9999995475819674, \"rank\": 4.524180934197481e-07, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}, {\"begin\": 3870, \"end\": 3876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7996914340187177, \"rank\": 0.16846884802379702, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Iowa does not have an Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3892, \"to\": 3931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3896, \"end\": 3900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming at Iowa beaches is one of the recreational attractions in a state without mountains and seashores.\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 4039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3944, \"end\": 3948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.7367592762326985e-24, \"text\": \"Iowa\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iowa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And whether we like it or not, water quality that discourages swimming, kayaking and fishing are activities that should concern people who call this state home or who come to visit us.\", \"from\": 4041, \"to\": 4225, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Or, it should.\", \"from\": 4227, \"to\": 4241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"--  Randy Evans is the executive director  of the Iowa Freedom of Information Council.\", \"from\": 4243, \"to\": 4329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4247, \"end\": 4258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Evans\", \"score\": 0.9999985100591589, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Randy Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Randy_Evans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He can be reached at DMRevans2810@gmail.com.\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thanksgiving Day took root in our nation's history as a \\\"day of public thanksgiving and prayer\\\" when George ...\", \"from\": 4376, \"to\": 4487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the text of the Iowa Constitution lacks the prominence of that adopted by our nation's Founding Fathers, ...\", \"from\": 4489, \"to\": 4603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4582, \"end\": 4598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Founding_Fathers_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1936430763235428e-20, \"text\": \"Founding Fathers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Founding_Fathers_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Founding_Fathers_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The central scandal in the Epstein's sex abuse ring targeting children is not the sex.\", \"from\": 4605, \"to\": 4691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the children.\", \"from\": 4692, \"to\": 4710, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"...  My place of prayer and meditation is the bathroom, precisely, sitting on the stool, and has been for the 36 years I ...\", \"from\": 4711, \"to\": 4835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025 Marshalltown Newspaper, LLC | https://www.timesrepublican.com | 135 West Main Street, Marshalltown, IA 50158 | 641-753-6611\", \"from\": 4839, \"to\": 4979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4856, \"end\": 4868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marshalltown_High_School\", \"score\": 0.9999999997044142, \"rank\": 2.9348361991293076e-10, \"text\": \"Marshalltown\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marshalltown_High_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marshalltown_High_School\"}, {\"begin\": 4880, \"end\": 4883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999999323117686, \"rank\": 6.768845567534282e-08, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}, {\"begin\": 4942, \"end\": 4958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marshalltown,_Iowa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marshalltown, IA\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marshalltown